==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: normative
<hw>normative</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>relating to or
dealing with norms; <as>as, <ex>normative</ex> discipline;
<ex>normative</ex> samples</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Grammar)</fld> <def>giving directives or rules;
prescriptive. Opposed to <ant>descriptive</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> prescriptive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>based on or prescribing a norm or standard; <as>as,
<ex>normative</ex> grammar</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>normotensive</ent>⟦br⟧
